Initialize CTS Module State

Source: R/CTS_Server.R
CTS_init_state.Rd

Creates a list of the initialized module state

Usage

CTS_init_state(FM_yaml_file, MOD_yaml_file, id, id_MB, session)

Arguments

FM_yaml_file

App configuration file with FM as main section

MOD_yaml_file

Module configuration file with MC as main section

id

ID string for the module

id_MB

An ID string that corresponds with the ID used to call the MB modules

session

Shiny session variable

Value

list containing an empty CTS state

Examples

# Within shiny both session and input variables will exist,
# this creates examples here for testing purposes:
sess_res = CTS_test_mksession(session=list())

#> 1                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                MB_obj_1_fcn = function () \n{\n    description <- "One compartment PK model with linear clearance using differential equations"\n    ini({\n        lka <- 0.45\n        label("Absorption rate (Ka)")\n        lcl <- 1\n        label("Clearance (CL)")\n        lvc <- 3.45\n        label("Central volume of distribution (V)")\n        propSd <- c(0, 0.5)\n        label("Proportional residual error (fraction)")\n    })\n    model({\n        ka <- exp(lka)\n        cl <- exp(lcl)\n        vc <- exp(lvc)\n        kel <- cl/vc\n        d/dt(depot) <- -ka * depot\n        d/dt(central) <- ka * depot - kel * central\n        Cc <- central/vc\n        Cc ~ prop(propSd)\n    })\n}\nMB_obj_1_rx =  rxode2::rxode2(MB_obj_1_fcn)
#> 2 MB_obj_2_fcn = function () \n{\n    description <- "Two compartment PK model with linear clearance for average monoclonal antibodies (Davda 2014)"\n    reference <- "Davda JP, Dodds MG, Gibbs MA, Wisdom W, Gibbs JP. A model-based meta-analysis of monoclonal antibody pharmacokinetics to guide optimal first-in-human study design. MAbs. 2014;6(4):1094-1102. doi:10.4161/mabs.29095"\n    ini({\n        lfdepot <- -0.295714244149045\n        label("Subcutaneous bioavailability (fraction)")\n        lka <- -1.26584820804402\n        label("Absorption rate (Ka, 1/day)")\n        lcl <- -1.6094379124341\n        label("Clearance (CL, L/day)")\n        lv <- 1.28370777234479\n        label("Central volume of distribution (V, L)")\n        lvp <- 1.01160091167848\n        label("Peripheral volume of distribution (Vp, L)")\n        lq <- -0.29169009384932\n        label("Intercompartmental clearance (Q, L/day)")\n        allocl <- 0.865\n        label("Allometric exponent on clearance and intercompartmental clearance (unitless)")\n        allov <- 0.957\n        label("Allometric exponent on volumes of distribution (unitless)")\n        prop.err <- c(0, 0.144)\n        label("Proportional residual error (fraction)")\n        etafdepot ~ 0\n        etaka ~ 0.416\n        etacl + etav + etavp ~ c(0.0987, 0.0786, 0.116, 0.0377, \n            0.0619, 0.0789)\n        etaq ~ 0.699\n    })\n    model({\n        fdepot <- exp(lfdepot + etafdepot)\n        ka <- exp(lka + etaka)\n        wtnorm <- log(WT/70)\n        cl <- exp(lcl + allocl * wtnorm + etacl)\n        q <- exp(lq + allocl * wtnorm + etaq)\n        v <- exp(lv + allov * wtnorm + etav)\n        vp <- exp(lvp + allov * wtnorm + etavp)\n        Cc <- linCmt()\n        f(depot) <- fdepot\n        Cc ~ prop(prop.err)\n    })\n}\nMB_obj_2_rx =  rxode2::rxode2(MB_obj_2_fcn)
